e necessities of the moment and governance norms and policies should be assessed in the context of historical events. They also demonstrate that successful reform depends on the artful consideration of technological, financial, and cultural developments. Locus of Authority shows that the consequences of not addressing college and university governance are more than the nation can afford.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Mai 2019) 0aEducation, HigherzUnited StatesxAdministration. 0aTeacher participation in administrationzUnited States. 0aUniversities and collegeszUnited StatesxAdministration. 0aUniversities and collegeszUnited StatesxFaculty. 7aEDUCATION / Higher.2bisacsh1 aTobin, Eugene M., eauthor.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPUP eBook-Package Pilot Project 2014-2015z978311044418608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPUP eBook-Package Pilot Project 2014-2015z978311066592540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781400865635zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781400865635.jpg  a978-3-11-044418-6  PUP eBook-Package Pilot Project 2014-2015  a978-3-11-066592-5  PUP eBook-Package Pilot Project 2014-2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aPDA7ENG  aPDA9PRIN